You have/had your own ideas (such as vegetarianism) which are not based in
Judaism. No one cares what you eat, but you periodically post to SCJM
asserting that vegetarianism is *based on torah*, and every time you do
that, you are corrected. I can't recall some of the other things you've
posted, but the vast majority of what you post is your own worldview which
is not related to torah. No one here has an objection to your worldview. The
objection is when you incorrectly state that this or that is *Jewish
thought* and *based on torah* when it's simply your own ideas and often the
total opposite of what the torah says. The correction of incorrect ideas is
not a personal attack.

Yet, in the past (just as now) you have generated an ongoing series of posts
where you complain that people are being mean to you and hate you and that
we are all Jews and then you bring the Holocaust into the equation. Sorry,
but you cannot expect the people on this newsgroup to be intellectually
dishonest out of fear that someone is going to complain (yet again) that
everyone is being mean to him. Disputing your incorrect understanding of
what is Jewish thought versus what is secular politically correct thought is
not &quot;a mean-spirited attack&quot; and constantly complaining that people are
&quot;being mean&quot; in an effort to get them to shut up is a manipulative tool. My
11-year-old son has been using this manipulation for years. I'm truly sorry
that you or your relatives experienced the horrors of the Holocaust but
speeches about &quot;Jews need to be unified&quot;  and &quot;we need to support each
other&quot; doesn't obligate us to agree that the torah endorses vegetarianism
just to avoid having you generate yet another post where you tell us how
mean we all are.
Best regards,
----Cindy S.

